11#ifndef MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_RTP_VP9_REF_FINDER_H_
12#define MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_RTP_VP9_REF_FINDER_H_
13
14#include <deque>
15#include <map>
16#include <memory>
17#include <set>
18
19#include "absl/container/inlined_vector.h"
20#include "modules/video_coding/frame_object.h"
21#include "modules/video_coding/rtp_frame_reference_finder.h"
22#include "rtc_base/numerics/sequence_number_util.h"
23
24namespace webrtc {
25
26class RtpVp9RefFinder {
27 public:
28 RtpVp9RefFinder() = default;
29
30 RtpFrameReferenceFinder::ReturnVector ManageFrame(
31 std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame);
32 void ClearTo(uint16_t seq_num);
33
34 private:
35 static constexpr int kFrameIdLength = 1 << 15;
36 static constexpr int kMaxGofSaved = 50;
37 static constexpr int kMaxLayerInfo = 50;
38 static constexpr int kMaxNotYetReceivedFrames = 100;
39 static constexpr int kMaxStashedFrames = 100;
40 static constexpr int kMaxTemporalLayers = 5;
41
42 enum FrameDecision { kStash, kHandOff, kDrop };
43
44 struct GofInfo {
45 GofInfo(GofInfoVP9* gof, uint16_t last_picture_id)
46 : gof(gof), last_picture_id(last_picture_id) {}
47 GofInfoVP9* gof;
48 uint16_t last_picture_id;
49 };
50
51 FrameDecision ManageFrameInternal(RtpFrameObject* frame);
52 void RetryStashedFrames(RtpFrameReferenceFinder::ReturnVector& res);
53
54 bool MissingRequiredFrameVp9(uint16_t picture_id, const GofInfo& info);
55
56 void FrameReceivedVp9(uint16_t picture_id, GofInfo* info);
57 bool UpSwitchInIntervalVp9(uint16_t picture_id,
58 uint8_t temporal_idx,
59 uint16_t pid_ref);
60
61 void FlattenFrameIdAndRefs(RtpFrameObject* frame, bool inter_layer_predicted);
62
63 // Save the last picture id in order to detect when there is a gap in frames
64 // that have not yet been fully received.
65 int last_picture_id_ = -1;
66
67 // Frames that have been fully received but didn't have all the information
68 // needed to determine their references.
69 std::deque<std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject>> stashed_frames_;
70
71 // Where the current scalability structure is in the
72 // |scalability_structures_| array.
73 uint8_t current_ss_idx_ = 0;
74
75 // Holds received scalability structures.
76 std::array<GofInfoVP9, kMaxGofSaved> scalability_structures_;
77
78 // Holds the the Gof information for a given unwrapped TL0 picture index.
79 std::map<int64_t, GofInfo> gof_info_;
80
81 // Keep track of which picture id and which temporal layer that had the
82 // up switch flag set.
83 std::map<uint16_t, uint8_t, DescendingSeqNumComp<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>>
84 up_switch_;
85
86 // For every temporal layer, keep a set of which frames that are missing.
87 std::array<std::set<uint16_t, DescendingSeqNumComp<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>>,
88 kMaxTemporalLayers>
89 missing_frames_for_layer_;
90
91 // Unwrapper used to unwrap VP8/VP9 streams which have their picture id
92 // specified.
93 SeqNumUnwrapper<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength> unwrapper_;
94
95 SeqNumUnwrapper<uint8_t> tl0_unwrapper_;
96};
97
98} // namespace webrtc
99
100#endif // MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_RTP_VP9_REF_FINDER_H_
